ExpressRoute failover is widely used in real-world enterprise environments.

For example, a banking system uses dual ExpressRoute circuits to ensure that if one fails, the backup circuit maintains connectivity.

A real-life use case is stock trading platforms where even a few seconds of downtime can result in financial loss.

Another example is healthcare systems where continuous access to patient data is critical.

Global enterprises also use failover to maintain operations across multiple regions.

These implementations ensure business continuity and reliability.
